Prior’s Century Helps England to 486 in 2nd Test With Sri Lanka

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-06-04T13:09:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-04/prior-s-century-helps-england-to-486-in-2nd-test-with-sri-lanka.html
Matt Prior’s century helped England
reach 486 all out on day 2 of the second cricket Test with  Sri
Lanka .  Prior scored 126 at Lord’s in  London . He teamed with  Stuart
Broad  (54) for a stand of 108 as England added to its overnight
first-innings score of 342-6.  Chanaka Welegedara took four wickets and Suranga Lakmal
claimed three after Sri Lanka won the toss and elected to field.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  